<div class="en">
<svg viewBox="0 0 700 430" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="width:100%;height:auto;background:#111113;border-radius:12px;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.08);margin:20px 0">
  <text x="20" y="32" fill="#fafafa" font-size="16" font-weight="700" font-family="sans-serif">Two Lawsuits, Two Endings — Jarrett vs. Paschall</text>
  <g font-family="sans-serif">
    <rect x="20" y="55" width="300" height="150" rx="10" fill="#18181b" stroke="#3f3f46" stroke-width="1"/>
    <text x="35" y="80" fill="#fbbf24" font-size="14" font-weight="700">The Jarretts (Tezos staking)</text>
    <text x="35" y="105" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">Received 2019 rewards, paid tax, sued for refund</text>
    <text x="35" y="128" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">Represented by counsel, organized fight</text>
    <text x="35" y="151" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">IRS mailed refund check → case mooted</text>
    <text x="35" y="174" fill="#f87171" font-size="13" font-weight="700">→ 2023: Sixth Circuit dismisses as moot (unresolved)</text>
    <text x="35" y="194" fill="#38bdf8" font-size="12">→ "Jarrett 2.0" pending for 2020 tax year</text>

    <rect x="380" y="55" width="300" height="150" rx="10" fill="#18181b" stroke="#3f3f46" stroke-width="1"/>
    <text x="395" y="80" fill="#fbbf24" font-size="14" font-weight="700">The Paschalls (Cardano staking)</text>
    <text x="395" y="105" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">Failed to report $33,354 in 2021 rewards</text>
    <text x="395" y="128" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">Pro se, no lawyer, no full trial</text>
    <text x="395" y="151" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">No expert testimony at all</text>
    <text x="395" y="174" fill="#4ade80" font-size="13" font-weight="700">→ June 2026: Tax Court rules for IRS (merits decided)</text>
    <text x="395" y="194" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="12">→ But non-precedential T.C. Memo</text>

    <rect x="20" y="225" width="660" height="60" rx="10" fill="#18181b" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="1"/>
    <text x="350" y="250" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">Two couples argued the same theory (tax at sale) — the IRS only won the fight it could win</text>
    <text x="350" y="270" fill="#e4e4e7" font-size="13" text-anchor="middle">If "Jarrett 2.0" reaches an appellate ruling, it could reach a different conclusion than Paschall</text>

    <rect x="20" y="300" width="660" height="110" rx="10" fill="#1e1b30" stroke="#8b5cf6" stroke-width="1"/>
    <text x="35" y="325" fill="#c4b5fd" font-size="13" font-weight="700">Meanwhile, Congress is moving the opposite way</text>
    <text x="35" y="348" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">Digital Asset PARITY Act (introduced May 19, 2026; Ways &amp; Means hearing June 9)</text>
    <text x="35" y="371" fill="#d4d4d8" font-size="13">→ Would let taxpayers elect to defer staking/mining reward tax up to 5 years</text>
    <text x="35" y="394" fill="#a1a1aa" font-size="12">Industry pushing back that the 5-year cap is too short</text>
  </g>
  <text x="350" y="422" fill="#71717a" font-size="12" text-anchor="middle" font-family="sans-serif">Sources: Tax Court T.C. Memo. 2026-46, Justia, CryptoBriefing, crypto.news · as of July 8, 2026</text>
</svg>
</div>
